            <title>[SPARK-22788] HdfsUtils.getOutputStream uses non-existent Hadoop conf &quot;hdfs.append.support&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22788</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Code: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;        if (conf.getBoolean(&quot;hdfs.append.support&quot;, false) || dfs.isInstanceOf[RawLocalFileSystem]) {
          dfs.append(dfsPath)
        } else {
          throw new IllegalStateException(&quot;File exists and there is no append support!&quot;)
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This makes the exception to be thrown if you enable &lt;tt&gt;writeAheadLog.closeFileAfterWrite&lt;/tt&gt; with HDFS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct config, from &lt;tt&gt;DFSConfigKeys&lt;/tt&gt;, is &lt;tt&gt;dfs.support.append&lt;/tt&gt;, and the default value is true.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
